00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:44,360
Then I made up some ba gua for her.
[*'Ba gua' also means gossip in Chinese]

869
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:47,440
And tied it on her head.

870
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:50,920
He made up a piece of gossip
and tied it on my head.

871
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:52,200
He made braids for me.

872
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,520
She wears it every day.

873
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:54,944
So it's making gossip concrete?

874
00:26:56,040 --> 00:26:57,400
Right, but the braids certainly...

875
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:59,160
The ba gua part is accurate.

876
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,440
I think it's accurate.

877
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,440
Alright, reasonable.

878
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:03,760
As long as we can
explain it away, it's fine, right?

879
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:04,320
(Whatever)
Reasonable.

880
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:05,040
No problem.

881
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:07,080
Count the word 'braids' for them.

882
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:08,560
Come on, the correct answer.

883
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,040
Would it still count if I said it?

884
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:10,960
It counts.

885
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:11,760
Go ahead.

886
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:12,520
Sun Honglei.

887
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:14,440
Handstands.

888
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:16,600
Handstands?

889
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:17,120
Handstands?

890
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:21,040
Handstand.

891
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:25,040
Handstands and puts
Wang Yuwen's hair in braids.

892
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:25,720
Braids.

893
00:27:26,640 --> 00:27:27,320
Braids.

894
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,160
- Handstands and puts Wang Yuwen's...
- And the last part.

895
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,960
And laughs wildly.

896
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:37,520
Too hard.

897
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:41,360
How many characters?

898
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:41,960
Six characters.

899
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:43,560
'Wang Yuwen' and 'Sun Honglei.'
Six characters are right.

900
00:27:43,776 --> 00:27:48,160
(Sun Honglei handstands, puts
Wang Yuwen's hair in braids, and laughs wildly)

901
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:51,880
We checked every character one by one.

902
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:52,480
Fireworks.

903
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:54,800
No 'fireworks.' It's 'firecrackers.'

904
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:55,680
Firecrackers.

905
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:56,040
Character 'bian'...
[*'firecrackers' and 'braids' sound the same]

906
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:57,360
'Bian' is here.

907
00:27:58,120 --> 00:27:59,280
('Bian')
Character 'bian' from 'firecrackers.'

908
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:01,920
We can count it as seven. And then?

909
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,640
Character 'fa.'

910
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,680
'Fa' wasn't said.

911
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,752
As 'fa' in 'making a phone call.'

912
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:13,000
Even if we count that,
we still can't win.

913
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:13,520
Let's go.

914
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:14,920
Admit defeat.

915
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:18,040
Even if we count that,
it still won't do.

916
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:19,800
Just count it.

917
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,400
'Wildly,' like character 'dian' in TV.

918
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,080
Naiwen.

919
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:23,840
That makes eight.

920
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,840
Naiwen, keep some dignity.

921
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:29,600
We're off by quite a bit.
